chocolate chocolate chunk cookie recipe does anyone have a really good chocolate chocolate chunk cookie recipe one of my friends at work loves chocolate and i thought i would make her cookies for her bday but i want a really good recipe one that has lots of chocolate and is soft if anyone has one i would really appreciate it thanks ultimate chocolate chocolate chunk cookie recipe ingredients pound semisweet chocolate chopped cups all purpose flour cup dutch process cocoa powder teaspoons baking powder teaspoon salt tablespoons unsalted butter cups packed brown sugar cup white sugar eggs teaspoons instant coffee granules teaspoons vanilla extract directions melt chocolate over a double boiler or in the microwave stirring occasionally until smooth sift together flour cocoa baking powder and salt set aside in a medium bowl cream butter with white sugar and brown sugar until smooth beat in eggs one at a time then stir in coffee crystals and vanilla until well blended stir in melted chocolate using a wooden spoon stir in the dry ingredients just until everything comes together cover and let stand for minutes so the chocolate can set up preheat the oven to degrees f degrees c line two cookie sheets with parchment paper roll dough into walnut sized balls or drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto the prepared cookie sheets leaving inches between cookies bake for to minutes in the preheated oven cookies will be set but the centers will still be very soft because of the chocolate allow cookies to cool on the baking sheets for minutes before transferring to wire racks to cool completely Japanese cuisine Chocolate Salty Balls Ice cream Cake Cocoa Flour Rice pudding Jewish cuisine Haggis Idli Chili con carne Oreo Puff pastry Pancake Tea Breakfast Mayonnaise Cuisine of Denmark Bagel Turkish coffee Sugar Halva Souffl__ Tofu Brewery Hot chocolate Cookware and bakeware Dairy Kraft Dinner Baked Alaska Cheesecake Baking powder Cuisine of Brazil Hot dog Baking Twix Recipe Confectionery Cu